Sunday. Kael raid. Long time in getting to Arena, and then even more delays. People have to leave, people joining, etc. I am in a group of 5, me as healer and 4 tanks. We then get a 48 or so Druid. Fine I think, he can nuke while I heal with Sup Heal (I'm level 52). Next giant comes along he SNARES!!!! I'm like, Man, don't snare it, there's a main snarer and snare is a lot of aggro so soon into the fight. No response. Next giant, he snares again. I repeat my comment and he says he's doing it for faction. Nuke I tell him. AFTER the giant is at half health, and maybe that way we can also start KSing, hehe :P<br>
Well, I dunno what he was doing next few fights, but he was definitely not nuking. Then there's a bad pull. One of my tanks begins taking a beating, so I heal. His health drops some more so I heal again... and get aggro of course. At this time I look at my group window and see the other druid is not in the same zone. WTF?? I say to myself. I am always permanently looking at Group window to see who's health drops a pixel and his definitely didn't. Well I get killed by the Protector of Zek and when I reappear at my bind the druid has disbanded from the group. I send him a tell: Did you gate?<br>
He responds: Yes, I had aggro so I gated.<br>
I'm thinking to myself: He had aggro? From doing WHAT? And he managed to pull off gate at level 48 with a Zek beating on him?? Does he think I'm stupid or what?<br>
I tell him: You DO NOT gate in the middle of a raid, and you DID NOT have aggro.<br>
- I had scrolled up my message window and saw just before I cast the second heal on my tank ' &quot;Druid&quot; begins to cast a spell' -<br>
I tell those in my group and they said they also thought they saw him gate.<br>
At that moment he sends me another tell: I didn't want to die so I gated. And it is dinner time anyway.<br>
Furious like hell I tell him if I ever see him on a raid again I will shout to the zone I will not raid with such a bad player and inform the raid leader it is him or me....<br>
&quot;Druid&quot; is not online at this moment.<br>
<br>
No comment.<br>
<br>
So when I finally get rezzed I tell all those at the raid what hapenned and that I will never raid with him again.<br>
<br>
What would you guys do?<br>
What do you think of this kind of behaviour?<br>
<br>
Just had to rant about it. He made me furious, and it's people like that that give us Dr00ds bad names.<br>
<br>
Ciao for now! <p>Araxx - 52 Wanderer<br>
Bristlebane<br>
Did you die?<br>
No, I'm a Druid, I don't die, I just get chased a lot.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/3/01 5:53:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/DAoC/lynxhead.jpg WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gating Druid... Grrrr</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't raid with him again.  I personally feel that all members of a raid have a responsibilty, and that is to keep raiders informed of your status, be it mana or allotted playing time.  He also should have been obedient to the raid leaders and organizers.  In this case, since you two were splitting up the chores, he should either adhere to his duties or tell you his intentions to do otherwise in advance.<br>
<br>
A raid is a team effort and if someone cannot follow orders or is not responsible enough to inform the raiding party that they must depart, you don't need them on the raid.  They are a liability, not an asset.  A raid depends on each individual who attends, and a person who gates in the middle of a battle without warning or instructions to do so is NOT dependable. <p><CENTER>
