I've had an experience recently..or rather my irl boyfriend has with a &quot;gater&quot;.<br>
<br>
To sum it up:<br>
He (Warrior) heads down to Lguk with a Cleric, Wizzy, and Shaman (will refer to this shaman as &quot;Peg&quot;), and two pick ups-another Shaman and a Monk.<br>
<br>
It gets a little rough down there, add after add.<br>
Cleric and pick up Shaman are OOM . Group asks &quot;Peg&quot;, what mana is and she says &quot;I told you 4 minutes ago I was OOM!&quot; and still continues to melee.<br>
Pick up ppl tell her to sit down and med for heals, but she still keeps poking at the frogs.<br>
Next thing I see is &quot;Loading Please Wait..&quot; on my boyfriend's monitor.<br>
Apparently everyone died except for the monk (FD) and &quot;Peg&quot; who mysteriously survived. After everyone died<br>
she told her group that the two pick up ppl were on each side of the zone training her.<br>
(I sent her a tell later asking how she survived. Apparently while the frogs were beating on her she memed gate and cast it-amazing how she survived all that..I mean when everyone died and monk FD'd the frogs would have all turned attention on her..and for her to be continously trained and still survive long enough to mem and gate at her low level-WOW! Needless to say I think she gated immediately once ppl started going down)<br>
Disgusted, the two pick ups disband.<br>
Warrior pops up along with Wizzy in FP (bindpoint) they have to run back down to Lguk to get corpses. Wizzy invis's them and Warrior grabs his corpse and drags it near the zone before he loots it. The others grab theirs, but the wizzies invis drops and within seconds she's dead. Cleric drops invis and is half dead by the time the warrior runs that way. Where is &quot;Peg&quot;? Oh..Peg was gated as soon as Wizzie bit the dust.<br>
Cleric dies. Warrior runs to zone with half health. Warrior is suppose to go and drag Cleric and Wizzies corpse to the zone. Will &quot;Peg&quot; come down and invis him so he can get the corpses? Hell no. Not wanting to wait the 2hours to regen the mass amount of hps, he zones back in with half health. He runs to the wizzies corpse and has about 8 frogs on him..he dies..again.<br>
Pops up in FP..again. Warrior sits there for about 20 minutes before &quot;Peg&quot; decides that her and the cleric can invis down there and revive everyone.<br>
 I found out that &quot;Peg&quot; does not like to invis because she does not want to take time to up her divination skills. Pity..heard from a friend she led a group into CC and refused to invis anyone on the lev down. Quite a train I heard, almost wiped out the party..<br>
This kind of idiocity drives me crazy..<br>
<br>
Course this is comming from me..a Shaman who's pet is getting beat on by Gen D'Veers in OT and making &quot;your next&quot; looks at me while I stay and make sure I reSoW my (unevil) group members so they might have a chance to make it to zone.<br>
<br>
<br>
Plaideous McGee<br>
Shaman of the 40th Season<br>
Zeb<br>
